ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take this course! One of the best I've taken at Yale. I wish I had taken this course before my senior year and had gotten to know Prof. Maralani more throughout my time at Yale because she is awesome!

I would definitely recommend this course to another student. You learn a lot about demography and you get to learn how to write sociologically (if you never have before). It is also a nice discussion because of the mix of graduate and undergraduate students.
